        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 12:48AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1248 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Mobeetie, or 18 miles southeast of Miami, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Mobeetie, Twitty, Mobeetie, Allison, Wheeler, Kellerville, and
Briscoe.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 167 and 176.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
